This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the usage of ensembles to improve the results of generative adversarial networks (GANs). It also involves the optimization of GAN objectives, which is a common topic in machine learning. 

The paper also involves the use of GANs for image generation, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper's focus on improving the results of GANs through ensembles suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper's use of self-ensembles and cascade GANs suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) as it involves the generation of images. 

Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and training of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
